reference_materials/
CLAUDE.md
# docker-compose bind-mounted controller state (./data) + optional caddy dirs
/data/
/caddy-data/
/caddy-config/
.dev-backend.log
.dev-backend.pid
.dev-frontend.log
.dev-frontend.pid
# Stray Go build artifacts emitted at the repo root by `go build ./cmd/...` (the binaries are
# released via the build pipeline, never committed from the tree).
/server
/compiler
/yaog-server
/yaog-compiler
/e2eserver
/e2eagent
# TEST-ONLY E2E bring-up binaries (plan-13): built into .e2e-bin/ by the verify step / the
# frontend-e2e CI job; resolved by the Playwright globalSetup. Never committed.
/.e2e-bin/
# WASM local engine (framework-refactor plan-3): the built wasm blob + the Vite static-asset
# copies are rebuilt by scripts/build-wasm.sh + the wasm-conformance CI job. Only the pinned
# runtime web/wasm_exec.js is committed (the gate asserts it matches the building toolchain).
/web/yaog.wasm
/frontend/public/yaog.wasm
/frontend/public/wasm_exec.js
# private key material must never be committed (bundle signing key, TLS, etc.)
*.pem
*.key
*.cred
# Exception: the localcompile contract corpus ships ONE throwaway test-only Ed25519 signing
# key (NOT any production key) so the signing-on golden fixture can byte-freeze the
# bundle.sig / signing-pubkey.pem path. It is generated under testdata and bound only to the
# test signer; see docs/spec/compiler/io-contract.md (the golden corpus).
!internal/localcompile/testdata/contract/signing/test-signing-key.pem